<p>I'm currently learning how to make a simple implementation of A* algorithm in Java. I find many of the tutorials difficult to follow. I just want to make a simple one without thinking about movement cost. So I found a pseudocode <a href="http://wiki.gamegardens.com/Path_Finding_Tutorial" rel="nofollow">here</a>, and trying to make the implementation from scratch.</p>  <p>I've made the mapArray which will read a file and store the characters into an array. Character A is the start, B is the goal and # is the walls. </p>  <pre><code>char[][] mapArray = new char[20][7];  public void readBoard() {      String everything = "";      try (BufferedReader br = new BufferedReader(new FileReader("map/map-1-1.txt"))) {         StringBuilder sb = new StringBuilder();         String line = br.readLine();         while (line != null) {             sb.append(line);             sb.append(System.lineSeparator());             line = br.readLine();         }         everything = sb.toString();     } catch (FileNotFoundException e) {         e.printStackTrace();     } catch (IOException e) {         e.printStackTrace();     }      String text = everything.replace("\n", "").replace("\r", "");     //System.out.println(text);       for (int i = 0; i &lt; 20; i++) {         mapArray[i][0] = text.charAt(i);         mapArray[i][1] = text.charAt(i + 20);         mapArray[i][2] = text.charAt(i + 40);         mapArray[i][3] = text.charAt(i + 60);         mapArray[i][4] = text.charAt(i + 80);         mapArray[i][5] = text.charAt(i + 100);         mapArray[i][6] = text.charAt(i + 120);     } } </code></pre>  <p>And then I have a method to detect the startnode, which is supposed to be inserted into the open list. But I don't know where to go on from here.</p>  <pre><code>public void getStartNode(){      int startpoint[] = new int[2];     for(int j=0; j&lt;7; j++){         for(int i=0; i&lt;20; i++){             if(mapArray[i][j]== 'A'){                 startpoint[0]= i+1;                 startpo